Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
assemble_proto_model(25.10)                        assemble_proto_model(25.10)

Name
       assemble_proto_model  -  Generate full chip FlexModel netlist by assem-
       bling FlexModel partition netlists back to the top-level design for hi-
       erarchical FlexModel generation

Syntax
       assemble_proto_model

       -topdir {topDesignDir [<protoModelDirName>]}

        [-blockdir {<blockDesignDir> [<protoModeldirName>]}]

        -mmmc_file <mmmcfileName>

        [-cpf_file <cpfFileName>]

       [-help]

       Generate full chip FlexModel netlist by assembling FlexModel  partition
       netlists back to the top-level design for hierarchical FlexModel gener-
       ation.  It  automatically  creates  a  full  chip  FlexModel  directory
       (proto_model) by merging back FlexModel information  of  all  specified
       partition blocks and assembling back into the top-level design.

       The  purpose for this command is to get a FlexModel netlist DB in chip-
       level by assembling the block and top data. This command may be used to
       help memory usage by not loading a full chip netlist  and  can  be  run
       from where you will run top-down hierarchical flow. This flow should be
       used if there are partition block netlists.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each assemble_proto_model parameter.

              For detailed description of the command and all its  parameters,
              use the man command: man assemble_proto_model .

       -blockdir {<blockDesignDir> [<protoModeldirName>]}
              Specifies  the path to block-level design. This directory should
              contain full netlist and FlexModel netlist  of  the  block-level
              design and the corresponding proto model directory. If you spec-
              ify  more than one block-level design, then you must specify the
              -blockdir option separately for each block-level design.

              protoModelDirName: Optional. Specifies the directory name  where
              FlexModel models can be found. The default directory name is re-
              trieved from the setting of set_proto_mode -create_dir parameter
              that  is specified before running assemble_proto_model. If -cre-
              ate_dir information is not available then the default  directory
              name  will  be  proto_model  at the current run directory. It is
              recommended  to  specify  <protoModelDirName>   especially   for
              -blockdir parameter.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -cpf_file
              Specifies  chip  level CPF file. This option should be specified
              for a design with power domain.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -mmmc_file
              Specifies chip level MMMC file.

              Data_type: string, optional

       <protoModelDirName>
              Optional. Specifies the directory name  where  FlexModel  models
              can  be  found. The default directory name is retrieved from the
              setting of set_proto_mode -create_dir parameter that  is  speci-
              fied  before running assemble_proto_model. If -create_dir infor-
              mation is not available then the default directory name will  be
              proto_model at the current run directory.

              It  is recommended to specify <protoModelDirName> especially for
              -blockdir parameter.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -topdir {topDesignDir [<protoModelDirName>]}
              Specifies the path to the top-level design directory.  This  di-
              rectory  should  contain top-level design netlist. If the design
              has Flexmodels then the top-level FlexModel netlist should  also
              be  found  in  this directory with the corresponding proto model
              directory.

              protoModelDirName: Optional. Specifies the directory name  where
              FlexModel models can be found. The default directory name is re-
              trieved from the setting of set_proto_mode -create_dir parameter
              that  is specified before running assemble_proto_model. If -cre-
              ate_dir information is not available then the default  directory
              name  will  be  proto_model  at the current run directory. It is
              recommended  to  specify  <protoModelDirName>   especially   for
              -blockdir parameter.

              Data_type: string, optional

Examples
              *

                The following command merges all models of partition block de-
                signs arb and tdsp_core to the top-level design DTMF_CHIP that
                does not have any FlexModels.

                assemble_proto_model -topdir {PTN_dir/DTMF_CHIP} \

                -blockdir          {          PTN_dir/arb/arb_modelgen.enc.dat
                PTN_dir/arb/proto_model } \

                -blockdir    {    PTN_dir/tdsp_core/tdsp_core_modelgen.enc.dat
                PTN_dir/tdsp_core/proto_model} \

                -mmmc_file viewDefinition.tcl

              *

                The   following   command  merges  model  of  partition  block
                ptn_wrapper to the top-level design dtmf_recvr_core  that  has
                FlexModel(s)

                assemble_proto_model    -topdir    {PTN/dtmf_recvr_core/model-
                gen.enc.dat proto_model} \

                -blockdir  {  PTN/ptn_wrapper/modelgen.enc.dat   PTN/ptn_wrap-
                per/proto_model } \

                -mmmc_file DBS/dtmf_recvr_core.enc.dat/viewDefinition.tcl

